<h2>INTERNAL COMMUNICATIONS</h2>

<div class="warning-box">
  <strong>Warning:</strong> This experience contains themes such as death, psychological decay, unreality, and unknown entities that some may find disturbing. Discretion is advised.
</div>

<h3>WHAT IS THIS?</h3>
<p>
“Do Not Access This Log” is a science fiction journaling experience set aboard a deep-space vessel, station, or outpost. As a crew member under Class IV emergency protocol, you’re required to record daily logs — written or spoken.
</p>
<p>
Something is wrong. A malfunction? A contagion? Or something worse? Each day for seven cycles, you’ll draw cards to guide your entry: technical failures, strange encounters, theories — or transmissions that aren’t yours.
</p>
<p>
There are fragments of another voice in the system — a presence you can’t quite explain. At the end of your logging period, your entries are archived. The crisis is not over. Someone else will continue the record. Whether the logs help anyone survive is… uncertain.
</p>

<h3>HOW TO START?</h3>
<p>
You are a crew member aboard a spacecraft, station, or outpost affected by a Class IV emergency. Your orders are clear: maintain personal logs for psychological stability and data recovery.
</p>
<p>
Start with your first log:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>&gt; Identify your role (engineer, helm officer, scientist, etc.).</li>
  <li>&gt; Describe the current state of the ship or station.</li>
  <li>&gt; Explain what you know — or what you’ve been told — about the emergency.</li>
  <li>&gt; Keep it professional. Or personal. Or both. You choose.</li>
</ul>
<p>
If this is not your first cycle, review your previous entries. If something feels… off, trust your instincts. They may be all you have left. Click “Begin Cycle” to get your prompts.
</p>

<h3>HOW TO PLAY?</h3>
<p>
Each cycle (day), you will receive three random prompts. You may use all three, just one, or none. Use the prompts as inspiration — or ignore them entirely. When your entry is complete, prepare for the next cycle. Repeat this for seven days.
</p>

<h3>SECURITY</h3>
<p>
This experience simulates isolation, fear, and unreality in a fictional sci-fi setting. Play within your comfort zone, and avoid including real personal information.
</p>
<p>
Your logs may be read or heard by others — be mindful of their potential impact. You are not required to share or pass on your log; let it drift if you choose. The Presence will find someone else.
</p>

<h3>MUSIC</h3>
<p>
A Spotify playlist is available to accompany your journaling experience and set the right mood for the story: http://bit.ly/dnatl
</p>

